                           --AMIGADOS GUIDE V2.6--
                               CUSTOM CHIPSET


   DESCRIPTION:
   As well as the CPU, the Amiga has Custom  Chips (designed specifically
   for the Amiga) which look after the graphics and sound.

   They are an integral part of the Amigas design which combined with the
   Operating System make the Amiga what it is.

   These chips all have names which are listed below:
    -Agnus      -Gary
    -Alice      -Buster
    -Paula
    -Denise


   NOTES:
   Their were 3 major revisions to the Amigas Chipset:

   OCS (Original Chipset)
   Was the first Chipset as used by the A500, A1000 and A2000 Amigas.

   ECS (Enhanced Chipset)
   A few Enhancements made including new screenmodes and more Chipram.
   Used by the A500+, A600 and A3000 Amigas.

   AGA (Advanced Graphics Architecture)
   A major update, many changes made including 32Bit data handling,
   improved graphics, more Chipram, improved sprite scaling and rotation
   capabilities.

